<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAR 92 / Election 1992: FT Election Share watch
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE STOCK market seemed to judge the Tories the net gainers from the
exchanges between the two parties over Labour's health broadcast. Shares
that might benefit from a Conservative victory rose by more than the FT-SE
100 index of big company shares, while stocks that might gain if Labour
formed a government dropped back. The steady advantage to Labour shown in
the first full week of the campaign has faded this week.
</TEXT>
