FT  27 MAR 92 / Election 1992: Labour's Scots lift
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A SYSTEM Three poll in The Herald in Glasgow today shows a six-point surge
in Labour support in Scotland to 44 per cent.
The Nationalists are 18 points behind on 26 per cent (24 last time). The
Tories, at 22 per cent, show no change, while the Liberal Democrats dropped
to 7 per cent (10).
