<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAR 92 / Election 1992: Talks issue fuels Ulster campaign
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE ELECTION campaign in Northern Ireland heated up yesterday over the issue
of the Anglo-Irish agreement and the future of inter-party talks, Tim Coone
writes.
The Rev Ian Paisley, Democratic Unionist party leader, launching his party's
manifesto, said 'the shutters will come down' on talks if any attempt is
made to put the union on the negotiating table. 'The union is not
negotiable. Full stop.'
His remarks run counter to those of Mr John Hume, leader of the Social
Democrat Labour party, at the launch of his party's manifesto on Wednesday,
that 'everything will be on the table', when talks resume after the
election.
</TEXT>
