<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
West German retail sales will increase by no more than 1.5 per cent in real
terms this year, Mr Hermann Franzen, president of the HDE retailers'
association, said yesterday, writes Christopher Parkes from Bonn.
The boom of early 1991 was snuffed out later in the year as increased taxes
and duties and the economic downturn took their toll, he said. Total sales
in the west were almost DM750bn (Pounds 262bn), representing a volume
increase of 8.6 per cent. Volume in the east, where there are no comparable
figures for 1990, reached around DM90bn.
