FT  27 MAR 92 / Bankers to roll over CIS debt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WESTERN bankers agreed yesterday to grant the former Soviet Union a further
90 days to start repaying the principal due on its foreign debt, Reuter
reports from Frankfurt.
The decision was announced by Deutsche Bank, which chairs a 12-bank panel
representing 600 banks worldwide, after talks between western bankers and
officials of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS). But the committee
won a promise from the CIS representatives to improve controls on their
export revenues, a key source of money for servicing the massive debt.
