   By CHARLES BATCHELOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SMALL businesses shed nearly 1m jobs in the two years to 1991, roughly half
the number created in the previous three years, according to a survey
published yesterday by the Small Business Research Trust, Charles Batchelor
writes.
Job losses have continued over the past nine months since the researchers
finished their work.
The recession has reduced the numbers of people working in businesses
employing up to 50 people by 16 per cent, the survey found. It based its
conclusions on a nationwide study of 120 small businesses in manufacturing
and service.
