<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 92 / Chinese envoy has disappeared, says embassy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CHINA'S embassy in London said yesterday that one of its diplomats had
disappeared but insisted his flight was caused by an extra-marital affair
and was not a defection, Reuter reports. The Home Office said a Chinese man
had asked for political asylum but did not name him.
An embassy official said a first secretary and his wife left the embassy
suddenly on March 18 and were still in Britain. The man's departure 'had
nothing whatsoever to do with politics,' the official said. 'Therefore
political asylum is out of the question.'
The official said the man's wife had asked several times that she and her
husband be allowed to cut short their posting and return to China.
</TEXT>
