<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 92 / Philippines expects return to GNP growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSE GALANG
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANILA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE PHILIPPINE government projects gross national product growth this year
of 2.5-3 per cent, after no growth last year.
Mr Cayetano Paderanga, economic planning secretary, yesterday briefed the
policy-making National Economic and Development Authority, which is headed
by President Corazon Aquino, on 'signs that the country is on its way to
recovery'.
He said growth in the domestic economy in the last quarter of 1991 'turned
slightly positive', compared to a 3.1 per cent fall in the third quarter.
Higher growth had come from increased public building, higher export
receipts, and heavy industrial re-stocking.
