FT  26 MAR 92 / Concern grows over Russia's N-plants
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ALL Russia's 400 nuclear power stations and research centres are a potential
danger, a safety official said yesterday, Reuter reports from Moscow. Mr
Sergei Shoigu, chairman of the State Committee for Civil Defence and
Emergencies, claimed Tuesday's radiation leakage at a nuclear power plant
near St Petersburg posed no danger, but criticism of the reactor type - the
same as that which exploded in Chernobyl in 1986 - was justified. In Vienna,
the International Atomic Energy Agency said it had downgraded the accident
to level-2 from level-3. Estonian foreign minister Lennart Meri complained
that radiation levels had doubled in the Estonian border town of Narva since
the leak.
