Gibbs and Dandy, the Luton-based building, engineering and electrical
distributor, remained in the red during 1991 as difficult trading conditions
in the construction industry continued to take their toll.
Operating profits dived from a restated Pounds 225,000 to Pounds 103,000,
and although interest charges were reduced, exceptional costs of Pounds
346,000 (Pounds 335,000) for redundancy and losses and provisions on
properties resulted in a pre-tax deficit of Pounds 754,000 (Pounds 757,000).
Turnover declined 10 per cent to Pounds 23.5m. Losses per share were 6.9p
(8.2p).
