intention but a small proportion has gone to large intermediaries.
The CU Environmental Trust will aim for long-term capital growth from
investments in companies which benefit from new environmental protection
expenditure.
There will be no geographical limitations.
Listing particulars were published yesterday for the issue of 17.5m ordinary
shares at 100p each, with warrants attached on a 1-for-5 basis providing the
right to buy shares at 100p at annual intervals over the next 10 years.
Dealings are expected to start next Friday, April 3.
The trust will be managed by CU Investment Management, which will receive an
annual management fee of 0.75 per cent, plus an initial fee of Pounds 40,000
(exclusive of VAT).
