FT  26 MAR 92 / University forms crisis group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY MORETON, Welsh Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE University of Wales has set up a 10-man committee under Sir Melvin
Rosser, a retired chartered accountant, to look at its future structure. The
move follows sharp disagreement over the shape of the university in the wake
of government funding changes.
Proposals by Sir John Meurig Thomas, deputy pro-chancellor, to sharpen the
university's federal structure were attacked by the heads of several
colleges amid accusations that Sir John was seeking to establish a tighter
central bureaucracy.
Sir John said last year that flaws existed in the way the university
operated. 'We now have a wonderful opportunity to take a federal university,
which is not really functioning as one, in a proper federal direction.'
That produced an outcry from the heads of the colleges and it was decided to
refer the matter of reorganisation and the relationship of the university to
other higher education institutes to a committee.
